<div class="bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-500 to-indigo-700 min-h-screen flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
  <div class="w-full max-w-lg bg-white shadow-md rounded-lg p-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">User Profile</h2>

    <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
      <img src="your_profile_image_url" alt="User Profile" class="rounded-full w-20 h-20 mr-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800"><%= current_user.username %></h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600"><%= current_user.email %></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-6">
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Hello! I'm <%= current_user.username %>, a passionate developer with a love for coding and problem-solving. I have a strong background in web development and a knack for creating responsive and user-friendly applications.

        My journey in the tech world began when I discovered my fascination for creating digital solutions. Since then, I've been on a continuous learning path, exploring various technologies and frameworks to stay up-to-date with the latest trends.

        With a keen eye for detail and a dedication to producing high-quality code, I'm committed to delivering top-notch software solutions. Whether it's front-end development, back-end development, or anything in between, I'm always up for a new challenge.

        When I'm not coding, you can find me enjoying a good book, hiking in the great outdoors, or experimenting with new recipes in the kitchen.

        Feel free to get in touch with me if you'd like to collaborate on a project or just have a chat. I'm always excited to connect with fellow developers and tech enthusiasts!
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-6">
      <button
        id="editProfileButton"
        class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-full focus:outline-none focus:shadow-outline"
      >
        Edit Profile
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="editProfileForm" class="hidden">
      <%= render 'form' %>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<script>
  // JavaScript to toggle the edit profile form
  const editProfileButton = document.getElementById('editProfileButton');
  const editProfileForm = document.getElementById('editProfileForm');

  editProfileButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
    editProfileForm.classList.toggle('hidden');
  });
</script>
